ly introduction that contextualises its visual and historiographic significance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aArchitecture, Ottoman. 4aArt. 4aMiddle East. 7aART / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aRoberts, Mary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilliams, Samuel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2024 Part 2z978311133238308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831110241270 cprintz978146324170440uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324503040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463245030423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463245030/original  a978-3-11-102412-7  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  a978-3-11-133238-3  DG Plus PP Package 2024 Part 2b2024  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles